# Hello, alt-markdown

This is a plain CommonMark document, and it already renders as alt-markdown
because the format is a strict superset.

- Lists work.
- **Bold** and _emphasis_ work.
- `inline code` works.

> Blockquotes work too.

Rich components (callouts, charts, diagrams) arrive as the standard library lands
in later phases. Until then, this file renders identically in any markdown reader.
